# ELMC 3D - 3D Modeling Platform from Geospatial Data

## Overview

ELMC 3D is a progressive web application (PWA) that allows users to generate, edit, and share 3D urban models based on real geospatial data from OpenStreetMap. Users can select a geographic area on an interactive map, choose desired element types (buildings, roads, water bodies, natural areas, landuse), and the system automatically generates an editable 3D model in GLB format.

## Features

- Interactive map with area selection using Leaflet
- Automatic 3D model generation from OpenStreetMap data
- Advanced 3D editor with granular element editing (Three.js)
- User authentication with JWT tokens
- Public workshop for sharing models
- Favorites system for public models
- Statistics tracking (views, downloads, favorites)
- PWA offline support with Service Worker
- RESTful API with Swagger documentation

## Technology Stack

- Backend: Django 5.2, Django REST Framework
- Database: MongoDB Atlas with MongoEngine ODM
- Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+), Three.js, Leaflet
- Authentication: JWT tokens stored in MongoDB
- PWA: Service Worker + Manifest.json
- API Documentation: OpenAPI 3.0 + Swagger UI + Redoc

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.11 or higher
- MongoDB Atlas account (or local MongoDB instance)
- Git

